Name: Roasted Vegetable Panini Bites
Description: This roasted vegetable panini with fresh mozzarella cheese and prosciuto is cut into bite-size pieces--a great way to use leftover grilled veggies!
Author: BelGioioso

Name: \Pantry Raid\ Chicken Enchilada Casserole
Description: With some chicken, a box of corn bread mix, and a few pantry items, you can whip up a tasty Mexican-inspired casserole.
Author: mama411

Name: Pork Chops Capri
Description: My grandma's recipe - pork chops simmered in a spicy tomato sauce with green beans and mushrooms. Wonderfully delicious, uses only one pan, and is easy to make. Enjoy!
Author: BRIDESTEIN

Name: Baked Egg Cups with Country Style Chicken Sausage
Description: Phyllo-dough cups filled with country style chicken sausage, eggs, and spinach and topped with shredded cheese are a delicious way to start your day!
Author: al fresco

Name: Chef John's Ham and Cheese Calzones
Description: These homemade calzones are stuffed with prosciutto, smoked ham, ricotta, and mozzarella cheese. Serve with marinara sauce for dipping, if desired.
Author: Chef John

Name: Banana Chocolate Chip Bread
Description: Very ripe bananas keep this quick bread sweet and moist.
Author: iggytakahashi

Name: Thai Fried Rice with Pineapple and Chicken
Description: This fried rice recipe with pineapple, chicken, and prawns is inspired by Thai street food and is a quick lunch or dinner.
Author: eatvancity

Name: Key Lime Cheesecake II
Description: Key lime cheesecake - sweet, tart and delicious! You may add 1 drop of green food coloring if desired. Garnish with whipped cream.
Author: Cindy Chaney

Name: Strawberry Beer Margaritas
Description: These beer margaritas get a flavorful twist with the addition of tequila-soaked strawberries!
Author: Arizona Desert Flower

Name: Cranberry Jalapeno \Cornbread\ Muffins
Description: Made with coconut flour, cranberries, and jalapeño, these pseudo cornbread muffins would make a great addition to a Thanksgiving table.
Author: Prestwood Family

Name: Paleo Coconut Lemon Cake
Description: Made with coconut and almond flour and bursting with lemon flavor, this cake makes an excellent low-carb, gluten-free, or Paleo treat.
Author: Megan Olson

Name: Taiwanese-Style Beef Noodles
Description: This beef with ramen noodles recipe adapted for the slow cooker is a hearty, crowd-pleasing version of the traditional Taiwanese soup.
Author: Anita Chen

Name: Taiwanese Popcorn Chicken
Description: Seasoned bite-sized pieces of chicken are fried twice and topped with Thai basil leaves in this Taiwanese-inspired popcorn chicken recipe.
Author: chelsea

Name: Summertime Dessert Lasagna
Description: Layers of graham crackers, banana pudding, ricotta cheese, and fresh kiwis and berries make this lasagna a cool summertime dessert.
Author: Kari Chappell

Name: Capirotada a la Antigua (Mexican Bread Pudding)
Description: Capirotada, a traditional Mexican dessert, is made with bread soaked in a spiced guava syrup and layered with raisins, cotija, and peanuts.
Author: gigi

Name: Poached Salmon Tobiko Bowls
Description: Sticky rice is topped with salmon and tobiko (fish eggs) in this quick and easy Japanese-inspired bowl that is ready in less than 1 hour.
Author: A Day In the Kitchen

Name: Taiwanese Spicy Beef Noodle Soup
Description: This Taiwanese beef noodle soup made with chiles, udon noodles, and plenty of garlic is easily made in the slow cooker for winter evenings.
Author: jhuang0125

Name: Hong Kong-Style Five Vegetable Fried Rice Noodle (Ng So Chao Mai Sin)
Description: Rice noodles stir-fried with mushrooms, cabbage, and cucumber in a soy sauce-based sauce is a quick Taiwanese-style vegetable noodle dish.
Author: Renita Au Yeung

Name: Chef V's Smoothie Bowl
Description: Fruit, coconut water, and Greek yogurt are blended together, poured into a bowl, and topped with chia seeds in this smoothie bowl recipe.
Author: Chef V

Name: Pretzel Broomstick
Description: String cheese, pretzel sticks, and spinach come together to make pretzel broomsticks, a clever snack the whole family will love on Halloween.
Author: medoDIYstuffs

Name: Chicken and Rice with Cumin and Cilantro
Description: Chicken wings are simmered with rice and lots of onion, ginger, garlic, and cilantro in this delicious one-pot meal, arroz con pollo.
Author: Jacques Pepin

Name: 1234 Taiwanese Spare Ribs
Description: With 1 pound spare ribs, 2 tablespoons vinegar, 3 tablespoons sugar, and 4 tablespoons soy sauce, this Taiwanese recipe is hard to forget.
Author: Jessica

Name: French-Style Lasagna
Description: Layers of creamy bechamel sauce and Swiss cheese add French-style touches to this beef lasagna that will elicit lots of compliments.
Author: Melody

Name: Philly Cheesesteak Lasagna
Description: This Philly cheesesteak lasagna is not your typical lasagna, loaded with flank steak, bell peppers, mushrooms, and four kinds of cheese.
Author: Lili Goehring

Name: Kristi's Chocolate Lasagna
Description: Crushed cookies, sweetened cream cheese, chocolate pudding, and mini chocolate chips are the building blocks of this no-bake dessert lasagna.
Author: Kristi Poole

Name: Raspberry Lemon Cream Cheese Waffles
Description: Fresh raspberries and lemon juice are the perfect pairing in these easy waffles with a little extra richness thanks to cream cheese.
Author: upandover

Name: Blackberry Focaccia with Sweet Ricotta Cheese
Description: Dress up store-bought pizza dough with fresh blackberries, rosemary honey, and sweetened ricotta cheese for a deliciously unique focaccia.
Author: JennM

Name: Blackberry Sage Prosecco Cocktail
Description: Prosecco wine, blackberry juice, and fresh sage leaves are all you need to make this unique sparkling cocktail with refreshing aromas.
Author: Cocktail Jim

Name: Chocolate Blackberry Bars
Description: These jammy double-crust bars with fresh blackberries are reminiscent of a cobbler, but have a surprise chocolate layer in the middle.
Author: FARNSWORTH
